tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cum1665702959588.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cum1665702959588.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cum1665702959588.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cum1665702959588\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Record Management on Oracle\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cum1665702959588__record_management_on_oracle_166137\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface can access and create tables with columns and constraints, indexes, and stored package specifications and stored package bodies. Uniface can also access views which have been defined in the application model.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cum1665702959588__p_d56384e1_d56385e1_d56386e1\">The limits imposed by Oracle on records, indexes, tables, and fields are shown in the table:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">ORA Connector Limits</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n What\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n Maximum\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n Comments\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Fields per record\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n 254 fields\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n Uniface only supports 253 fields in modifiable tables.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Length of record\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n 8KB\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n A Uniface record (not including segmented fields) has a maximum of 8192 bytes.\n <div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The maximum record size for entities that have variable length fields is 8KB, the rest goes into the overflow table. For entities with only fixed length fields the maximum record size is 2GB-1.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Fields per key\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n 16 fields\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Number of indexes\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n Unlimited\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Maximum length of key\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n Unlimited\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n A Uniface record has a maximum of 8192 bytes.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n Maximum length of a field\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n Not applicable\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n Dependent on the storage format.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__1\">\n SQL statement length\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__2\">\n 64 KB\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cum1665702959588__table_d5132e1_d5133e1_d5134e1__entry__3\">\n Uniface has a maximum of 10 kilobytes, except for the Create Table facility.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526627\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526627\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Record Management on Oracle Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Record Management on Oracle Uniface can access and create tables with columns and constraints, indexes, and stored package specifications and stored package bodies. Uniface can also access views which have been defined in the application model. The limits imposed by Oracle on records, indexes, tables, and fields are shown in the table: Table 1. ORA Connector Limits What Maximum Comments Fields per record 254 fields Uniface only supports 253 fields in modifiable tables. Length of record 8KB A Uniface record (not including segmented fields) has a maximum of 8192 bytes. Note: The maximum record size for entities that have variable length fields is 8KB, the rest goes into the overflow table. For entities with only fixed length fields the maximum record size is 2GB-1. Fields per key 16 fields Number of indexes Unlimited Maximum length of key Unlimited A Uniface record has a maximum of 8192 bytes. Maximum length of a field Not applicable Dependent on the storage format. SQL statement length 64 KB Uniface has a maximum of 10 kilobytes, except for the Create Table facility. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}